<br>
As for the Val raid thing, well that was the only time I actually went with them on a raid (well except a spur of the moment CT raid and a GD war).  As I said I was asked along to help so I was kind of surprised by that.  Especially since they were rolling on everything else.  Also all the healers except for I think Ogun were non Valoran.  Still, while I was upset with them I will admit that one experience an opinion doth not make.  And I guess I should be giving them more benefit of the doubt.  After all they dont know me from Adam so I wouldnt expect them to look out for me.  Not their job anyway.<br>
<br>
Anyway, if anyone gives you a problem tell them to post up here.  I have to say I havent had roast newbie in a longtime and I'm starting to get hungry.  No one should be questioning your right, or for that matter any past CoG member's right, to be on any raid KGC allows you to be on.  For nothing else the experience is welcome as is the friendship and company.  And yes, to roll if you want.  I may not agree with Ogun rolling or even that we needed him, but the rules were stated and he WAS there so deservered to roll.  No question.  You should be thanked for helping and not rolling.  Just dont let the jerks get ya down. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
